In article <1992Mar9.081248.14072@actrix.gen.nz>, Kris.Heidenstrom@bbs.actrix.gen.nz wrote:
}All techniques for shrouding an executable program can be defeated.  For
}example the above technique could be defeated simply by copying the code and
}modifying the first copy so that it does its CRC calculation on the copy. 
}You're then free to insert breakpoints etc wherever you want.

And don't forget that you can set breakpoints without modifying the code on
386's and up.  No need to even copy the code, just set a hardware breakpoint
(Breakpoints/Hardware/AccessMemory/AddressMatch-Equal/Value=???? in Turbo
Debugger).

